# ⏱️ Complexity Analysis

### Time Complexity

```text
O(n + m)
```

- One pass to find earliest finishing rides.
- One pass to evaluate both ride orders.

### Space Complexity

```text
O(1)
```

Only a few variables are used.

---

# 🧠 Key Insight

The optimal schedule only depends on:

```text
Earliest finishing land ride
Earliest finishing water ride
```

Rather than checking every pair of rides (`O(n × m)`), we can compute the answer in linear time by leveraging the earliest completion times of each category.

